10 celebration of National Poetry Month.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, the Academy of American Poets established the month of
14 April as National Poetry Month in 1996; and
15 WHEREAS, National Poetry Month seeks to highlight the
16 extraordinary legacy and ongoing achievement of American poets,
17 introduce Americans to the pleasures and benefits of reading poetry,
18 bring poets and poetry to the public in immediate and innovative
19 ways, and make poetry an important part of our children's education;
20 and
21 WHEREAS, National Poetry Month, under the leadership and
22 direction of the Academy of American Poets, is now the largest
23 literary celebration in the world; and
